str2: A primary particle; but, and, etc.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: Answer, bid, bring word, command. A primary verb; to speak or say.
To, towards, with. A strengthened form of pro; a preposition of direction; forward to, i.e. Toward.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A vine-dresser, gardener. From ampelos and ergon; a vine-worker, i.e. Pruner.

parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: See! Lo! Behold! Look! Second person singular imperative middle voice of eido; used as imperative lo!
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.

parse: Personal / Relative Pronoun - Genitive Masculine Singular
str2: Who, which, what, that.
Three. Or neuter tria a primary number; 'three'.
A year. Apparently a primary word; a year.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 1st Person Singular
str2: To come, go.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To seek, search for, desire, require, demand. Of uncertain affinity; to seek; specially, to worship, or to plot.
Probably from the base of harpazo; fruit, literally or figuratively.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
This; he, she, it.
A fig-tree. From sukon; a fig-tree.
And, even, also, namely.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: A prolonged form of a primary heuro, which heureo is used for it in all the tenses except the present and imperfect to find.
Therefore, then. Apparently a primary word; certainly, or accordingly.

parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: To cut out (off, away), remove, prevent. From ek and kopto; to exscind; figuratively, to frustrate.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: From kata and argeo; to be entirely idle, literally or figuratively.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Contracted from a primary word; soil; by extension a region, or the solid part or the whole of the terrene globe.
